OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1774793495
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G2/2
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sun 12 Apr to Sun 26 Apr
OL,6,FHigh pressure may be dominant early in
OL,7,Fthis period, which would bring plenty
OL,8,Fof dry and settled weather across the
OL,9,FUK, especially in the south. Any low
OL,10,Fpressure systems bringing wetter,
OL,11,Fwindier weather are most likely to
OL,12,Faffect the north. Into late April, low
OL,13,Fpressure patterns may become more
OL,14,Fprevalent, with more unsettled,
OL,15,Fchangeable conditions developing more
OL,16,Fwidely. Temperatures are likely to be
OL,17,Fclose to or slightly above normal.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
